<div class="about-wrap">
  <h1>About The Spatial Update</h1>

  <p>
    The Spatial Update is a map-based news site. Every story here is georeferenced —
    tied to real coordinates on a live, explorable map — instead of being locked
    inside a wall of text. Strikes, shipping lanes, borders, migration routes,
    economic chokepoints: if it happened somewhere, you can find it on the map
    and see exactly where.
  </p>

  <p>
    Each story combines a written narrative with layered map data — timelines,
    markers, and geographic context you can click through at your own pace.
    The goal is simple: help readers understand where events are actually
    happening, not just that they happened.
  </p>

  <p>
    Alongside the map, we publish a daily <a href="/paper/latest.html">Morning Edition</a>
    — a quick, text-first roundup of the day's most significant developments,
    for readers who want the news without opening the map.
  </p>

  <p>
    The Spatial Update is independently produced. There is no newsroom behind
    it — just one person mapping the news.
  </p>
</div>
